The paper deals with interference management in a two-tiered network, which involves communication theory, networking, and signal processing. The use of OFDMA and cognitive interference alignment techniques suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The focus on self-organizing small cells and distributed optimization algorithms may also suggest the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of numerical simulations and performance evaluations may suggest the Multimedia (cs.MM) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
